==English==
[[Category:English proper nouns]]
===Etymology===
From Hebrew Hannah, literally "grace".
In a Russian context is aphetic of Annina, dim. of Greek Anna.
 
===Pronunciation===
* NEE-na
* &#323;i-na

===Proper noun===
'''Nina'''

#A common female [[given name]].  
#Short form of names that end in -nina.
#Coincides with the Spanish word niña meaning "little girl".
#The Babylonian goddess of the watery deep and daughter of Ea.

